# Creating VPC's

1.  Navigate to VPC
2.  Create VPC
3.  Select VPC only
4.  ![df901a633401a1b6d938a8054e63f9cd.png](../../_resources/df901a633401a1b6d938a8054e63f9cd.png)
5.  Name: se--first-2tier-vpc
6.  IPv4 CIDR block --> IPv4 CIDR manual input
7.  IPv4 CIDR --> 10.0.0.0/16 -
8.  VPC encryption control : None
9.  Tags: default.
10. Click create VPC button
11. Select create VPC

&nbsp;

# Subnet settings

**Public subnet**

1.  Select subnets from side menu
2.  Select create subnet
3.  Add the previously created VPC or the desired VPC
4.  Name the public subnet using a logical convention. e.g. (se--first-2tier-vpc-public-subnet)
5.  Select Ireland for the availably zone -->Europe (Ireland) / eu-west-1a
6.  Public subnet IPv4 CIDR block: 10.0.2.0/24 (Must be smaller than the VPC selected)
7.  Tags: Default

**Private subnet**

1.  Select "Add new Subnet" button to make a private subnet
2.  Name subnet using a convention e.g. (se--first-2tier-vpc-private-subnet)
3.  Select Ireland for the availably zone but choose a different node to the public subnet
4.  Private subnet IPv4 CIDR block: 10.0.3.0/24
5.  Tags: Default
6.  Click --> "create subnets"

![](data:image/png;base64,)

# Internet gateway

1.  Select internet gateway from side menu
    
2.  Name the gateway using a standard naming convention
    
3.  Select create internet gateway
    
4.  Click actions --> "attach to VPC"
    
5.  Select the recently created or desired VPC
    

&nbsp;

# Route tables

1.  From VPC --> select route tables
2.  Name the route table
3.  Attach to relevant VPC
4.  Select create route table
5.  In explicit subnet associations -> edit subnet associations
6.  Select the public subnet previously created

&nbsp;

# Routes

1.  Navigate to "routes" tab
2.  Select "edit routes"
3.  Select "Add route"
4.  From the settings menu
5.  Destination: 0.0.0.0/0
6.  Target: Internet Gateway, Add your internet gateway - This allows any IP to communicate with our class app.
7.  Click "save changes"
8.  <img src="../../_resources/76785e53a4ff8f4b8c0aad81578022ee.png" alt="76785e53a4ff8f4b8c0aad81578022ee.png" width="593" height="259" class="jop-noMdConv">

**Access instances**

1.  SSH into the app, as "ubuntu"
2.  Update the environment variable, using the private IP Address, then confirm the environment variable change.
3.  `export DB_HOST=mongodb://PUBLIC_IP:27017/posts`
4.  ```
    printenv DB_HOST
    ```
    
5.  Change directory to `nodejs2-sparta-test-app-2025/app`
6.  Seed the database and start the app
7.  `node seeds/seed.js`
8.  `pm2 start app.js`
